To solve the addition of numbers in base 3, we can write them vertically and sum the digits column by column, carrying over when the sum is greater than 2. 

\[
\begin{array}{r}
\underline{ \phantom{0}2\phantom{1}2\phantom{2}1\phantom{1}2\phantom{0}1_{3}} \\
+\underline{2\phantom{0}0\phantom{1}1\phantom{1}2\phantom{0}2\phantom{2}1_{3}} \\
1\phantom{0}1\phantom{2}\phantom{1}3\phantom{1}1\phantom{2}0\phantom{1}2\phantom{1}2\phantom{2}0_{3} 
\end{array}
\]

So, \( 22112011_{3} + 2001120221_{3} = 1131201220_{3} \).